We recommended the following:

Require the Municipal General Services Officer (MGSO) to consolidate weekly the RIS for which supplies and materials were issued using the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) and submit to the OIC – Municipal Accountant;

Management require the MGSO and the Municipal Health Office to maintain complete stock cards of the inventories and conduct periodic reconciliation with the ledger cards;

Form an inventory committee and conduct physical count every six (6) months, prepare a Report of Physical Count of Inventories and submit it to the Office of the Auditor; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to effect the necessary adjusting entries to restore back to the inventory account the undistributed/unconsumed items at the end of the year.

