Direct the Municipal Treasurer to send a written notices to the payees one month before the checks become stale. Stale checks shall be reported and attached to the RCI prepared at the period of cancellation;
For improperly reported stale checks, require the Office of the Municipal Treasurer and the Office of the Municipal Accountant to provide evidence that the checks are not outstanding that they have been voided and no obligation exist; and
Direct the In-charge of Office, Office of the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjusting entries for stale checks.

We recommended the following:

The OIC – Municipal Accountant direct the concerned accounting personnel to maintain subsidiary ledger cards for each group of PPEs;


The Municipal General Services Officer direct the personnel in-charge of LGU properties to maintain the equivalent Property Card for PPE to account for the receipt and disposition of the same;

The Inventory Committee prepare a consolidated report of physical count for each group of PPEs using the prescribed formats in the GAM for LGUs; and

The OIC – Municipal Accountant reconcile PPE items in the reports of physical count for each group of PPEs with the accounting records, then, effect necessary adjustments to ensure fair presentation of the PPE accounts in the financial statements.

We recommended and Management agreed that:
The OIC – Municipal Accountant direct the concerned accounting personnel to maintain subsidiary ledger cards for each group of PPEs;
The Municipal General Services Officer direct the personnel in-charge of LGU properties to maintain the equivalent Property Card for PPE to account for the receipt and disposition of the same;
The Inventory Committee prepare a consolidated report of physical count for each group of PPEs using the prescribed formats in the GAM for LGUs; and
The OIC – Municipal Accountant reconcile PPE items in the reports of physical count for each group of PPEs with the accounting records, then, effect necessary adjustments to ensure fair presentation of the PPE accounts in the financial statements.

We recommended the following:

•	The Management/Accounting Unit keep custody of a copy of the MOA of each fund received from the National Government to ensure compliance to the requirements and to facilitate monitoring;

•	The Municipal Accountant-Designate revisit the terms and condition of the MOA regarding the unexpended balance of the fund and take the necessary action if said fund shall be returned to the source agency or be reverted to the unappropriated surplus of the implementing agency;

•	Quarterly monitoring shall be conducted by the Municipal Engineer in coordination with the Municipal Accountant to ensure proper implementation of projects and timely submission of the documents for liquidation to the source agency; and

•	The Municipal Accountant-Designate exert efforts to reconcile and prepare subsidiary ledgers/schedules for the Due to LGUs account as required under Section 114(2) of Presidential Decree (PD) No. 1445.

